10/09/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- A new terminal opened for business Wednesday (September 9th) at the only international airport in Albania -- the Mother Teresa International Airport. 
It will now be able to serve 1.8 million passengers, up 40% from its previous capacity. 
Prime Minister Sali Berisha, who attended the ceremony, said the airport is key to Albania's economic development. 
A total of 70m euros have been invested in it; the new terminal cost about 20m euros. 
(Alsat, Klan, Top Channel, Ora News, News 24 - 09/09/09)
